 Query Store Settings By:  Erin Stellato    Posted on: November 28, 2017 9:36 am  In SQL Server 2017 there are nine (9) settings related to Query Store.  While these are documented in  sys.database_query_store_options , I often get asked what the value for each setting “should” be.  I’ve listed out each setting below, along with the default value and considerations around changing the setting. 
   
 OPERATION_MODE 
 The default value for a new or upgraded database in SQL Server 2016 or SQL Server 2017 is OFF.  For Azure SQL Database, the default value is READ_WRITE. 
